        <section eId="sec_392_52">
          <num>392-52</num>
          <heading>Section 392-52</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§392-52  Disposition of accrued benefits
where insurer is unable to locate employee.
An insurer who is unable to
pay benefits to an employee because the employee cannot be located, shall
deposit the accrued benefits into the trust fund for disability benefits.  Upon
locating the employee, the director shall pay from the trust fund to the
employee an amount equal to but not more than the amount paid into the fund by
the employer.  If the employee cannot be located for a period of two years from
the date of deposit, the employee's unpaid benefits shall escheat to the trust
fund for disability benefits. [L 1981, c 115, §1; gen ch 1985; am L 2013, c
100, §8]
